latestPosts.caption:
Fabindia recently celebrated its 10th anniversary in Malaysia with a grand event at Royale Chulan Hotel, Kuala Lumpur. Since its Malaysian debut in 2015 at NU Sentral, the brand has expanded to three outlets under the leadership of Malaysia and Singapore franchise owner Datin Manjari, who also oversees operations in Singapore. The event was graced by several distinguished Guests of Honour, whose presence elevated the significance of the occasion. Among them were YB Tuan M. Kula Segaran, Deputy Minister in the Prime Minister's Department; Ms Shubashini Narayanan, Deputy Ambassador; Dato Vikness Raju; and Mr Ajay Kapoor, President – Retail at Fabindia HQ. With over 55,000 artisans connected globally, Fabindia remains committed to sustainability, cultural heritage, and conscious consumerism as it looks toward continued growth in the region.

📍Full story on lomp.at/fab10

latestPosts.caption:
Indian lifestyle and craft brand Fabindia has celebrated its 10th anniversary in Malaysia with a fashion showcase highlighting its blend of traditional textiles and contemporary design.

A reception at the Royale Chulan Bukit Bintang hotel on Saturday drew guests such as Deputy Minister in the Prime Minister’s Department (Law and Institutional Reforms) M. Kulasegaran, India’s Deputy Ambassador to Malaysia Shubashini Narayanan, Datuk Vikness Raju, and Ajay Kapoor, president of retail at Fabindia’s headquarters.

The event featured high tea, a lucky draw, and a runway presentation styled by R. Yogash, who is a well-known senior fashion stylist in Malaysia.

Titled “Showcasing Fabindia in Colour”, the show put 20 models in the brand’s signature outfits, underscoring its focus on handcrafted textiles, cultural heritage and sustainable fashion.

latestPosts.caption:
10 years of Craft, Culture and Connections.

It has been a decade since we first opened our doors in Malaysia — and what better way to mark this milestone than with a runway that brought our journey to life.

The evening unfolded in craft, colour, and classic silhouettes, an ode to the fabrics, weaves, and stories that have crossed borders, blending Indian heritage with Malaysian warmth.

Honoured by the presence of:
YB Tuan M. Kula Segaran, Deputy Minister in the Prime Minister’s Department
Ms. Shubashini Narayanan, Deputy High Commissioner of India to Malaysia
Dato’ Viknes Raju
Mr. Ajay Kapoor, President Retail, Fabindia Ltd.

Presented by:
Datin Manjari, Malaysia & Singapore Franchise Owner and Fabindia, Malaysia

Thank you for being part of this tapestry. Here’s to many more chapters to come.
